constructor.details: Marks the msg.sender as authorized and sets them      as the owner in authorization library

deauthorize(address).details: Privileged function to de authorize an address

params.who: The address to remove authorization from

deprecate().details: This contract holds a number of allowances for addresses so if it is deprecated      it should be removed so that users do not have to remove allowances.      Note - onlyOwner is a stronger check than onlyAuthorized, many addresses can be      authorized to freeze or unfreeze the contract but only the owner address can kill

isAuthorized(address).details: Returns true if an address is authorized

returns._0: true if authorized false if not

mint(uint256,address,uint256,address,(ad.details: This function assumes that it already has an allowance for the token in question.

params._amount: The amount of underlying to turn into tokens
params._expiration: The expiration time of the Tranche contract
params._permitCallData: Encoded array of permit calls to make prior to minting                        the data should be encoded with abi.encode(data, "PermitData[]")                        each PermitData struct provided will be executed as a call.                        An example use of this is if using a token with permit like USDC                        to encode a permit which gives this contract allowance before minting.
params._position: The contract which manages pooled deposits
params._underlying: Either (1) The underlying ERC20 token contract                   or (2) the _ETH_CONSTANT to indicate the user has sent eth.                   This token should revert in the event of a transfer failure.

returns._0: returns the minted amounts of PT and YT

setIsFrozen(bool).details: Allows an authorized address to freeze or unfreeze this contract

params._newState: True for frozen and false for unfrozen

withdrawWeth(uint256,address,uint256,uin.details: Allows a user to withdraw and unwrap weth in the same transaction      likely quite a bit more expensive than direct unwrapping but useful      for those who want to do one tx instead of two

params._amountPT: The amount of principal token to withdraw
params._amountYT: The amount of yield token to withdraw.
params._permitCallData: Encoded array of permit calls to make prior to withdrawing,                        should be used to get allowances for PT and YT
params._position: The contract which interacts with the yield bearing strategy

mint(uint256,address,uint256,address,(ad.notice: Mints a Principal/Interest token pair from either underlying token or Eth      then returns the tokens to the caller.
